         <abstract>
            <p>Water is variable and dynamic; feedwater differs in ionic composition depending on its source, location, and environmental changes. Because many kinds of scales may deposit on reverse osmosis (RO) membranes and within their feed channels, it's important to choose the correct antiscalant.</p>
